The Qinghai-Tibet Plateau turns into a desolate wilderness in winter. The limits of life are challenged by the harsh environment. The slightly warm valley there becomes a sanctuary for various animals such as the Tibetan wild ass, the blue sheep and the wild yak. Check out the video to learn about their stories of survival. About 'Journeys in Nature': Snowy Qinghai Lake Series Qinghai Lake, the largest saltwater, inland lake in China, is home to a large number of wild animals. CGTN Nature's film crew traveled to Qinghai and discovered rare animal and plant species. During the Spring Festival, we will present the beautiful nature of China â€“ "Journeys in Nature": Snowy Qinghai Lake Series, showing the wonderful creatures in winter. For more: Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 1: Snowy Lake Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 2: Swan lake on ice Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 3: Journey to the south Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 4: Battles for love Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 5: Broken dreams Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 6: Love on ice Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 7: Shrewd birds Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 8: Plateau mascot Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 9: Good neighbors (Cover image a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)